        <strong>3. Type directly.</strong> Enter any cron expression — including step values (<code class="ic">*/5</code>), ranges (<code class="ic">9-17</code>), and comma lists (<code class="ic">1,15</code>) — into the Expression field. The generator validates it instantly and syncs the dropdowns to match. Once you have your expression, switch between the <strong>Linux</strong>, <strong>AWS CloudWatch</strong>, <strong>GitHub Actions</strong>, and <strong>Kubernetes</strong> tabs to get the platform-specific format. The <strong>Next 10 Runs</strong> panel shows the next 10 execution times in your local timezone so you can verify the schedule is correct before deploying.
